n class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/thomei\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/d8ce2f7bd19daef219928e155269b6d8?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/d8ce2f7bd19daef219928e155269b6d8?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/thomei\" class=\"reviewer-name\">thomei</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">avril 3, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Otter offers some very useful options to Gutenberg. I really like the Otter-posts-block.\n\nBut we are looking for a full replacement of the \"Intergeo - Google Maps Plugin\". (see: https://de.wordpress.org/plugins/intergeo-maps/ ) Otter doesn\'t offer all the options of Intergeo maps, because we are unable to use Otter as a replacement. The development of Intergeo maps was unfortunately suspended.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">works smooth as silk</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 √©toiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 √©toiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/voltar99\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a76154